included.description: GLISAclimate.org is a website for people who are interested in Climate Science to collaborate together on a wide variety of  projects. While providing great amount of information, the website is facing many usability problems such as poor navigation, unorganized resource library and confusing editing page. We are doing Usability Test as well as Redesign for the website. We interviewed 10 users, conducted several Usability Tests, drew the Wire-frames in Balsamiq,  came up with pixel by pixel design in illustrator and right now are working on a clickable demon in InVision.
included.title: GLISAclimate Website Usability Test and Redesign - Client Project

included.description: The Michigan Institute for Clinical and Health Research (MICHR) is an institute affiliated with the University of Michigan whose mission is to enhance medical translational research. The Education Department within MICHR was struggling with the efficiency of their monthly newsletter. MICHR had especially low responding rate from their recipients: medical students and scholars. They wanted their resources to reach out to more medical students to help them with their research. However few people responded. We went to their workplace, interviewed relevant staff, examined their workflows, found several breakdowns and provided useful recommendations for improving their newsletter.
included.title: Analysis of Newletter at MICHR - Client Project

MPark is designed for University of Michigan students to find a parking space on campus. It is a mobile application that collects all the available parking information across the campus including university parking structure, roadside parking and public parking structure. It is a one-semester long individual project from the course of Intro to Interaction Design. The tools used for this project are mainly: Balsamiq + Proto.io + Photoshop.
included.title: MPark Mobile App Design - Individual Project

included.description: This is a long semester-long project from Needs Assessment and Usability Evaluation. Our client is Global Michigan( http://global.umich.edu/) whose  missions are branding University of Michigan internationally and providing exciting study abroad opportunities for current students. In this project, we utilized methods such as Comparative Analysis, Heuristic Evaluation and Usability Test to assess what the company need for improving their website's user experience and how should they approach these changes.
included.title: Global Michigan Usability Test - Client Project

included.description: This is what I did during my internship at the Office of Provost, University of Michigan last summer. I worked as a web designer along with another intern: Nicholas Lobaito. We did both research and design work for the provost website. We interviewed users to gain important information regarding the usability of the site. We then analyzed the interview summary, came to a conclusion about what we should develop and what we should abandon on the site. We drew the wire-frames and came up with this new design of the provost site. We also coded several pages to implement some changes.
included.title: Provost Site Redesign - Intern Project
